<div class="Y3BBE" style="font-family: &#39;Google Sans&#39;, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 16px 0px;">The solution moves away from a single, monolithic component towards a modular, data-driven, and loosely coupled architecture. This approach maximizes flexibility, eases future maintenance, and delivers an enhanced user experience without compromising upgradability.</div>
<div class="Y3BBE" style="font-family: &#39;Google Sans&#39;, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 16px 0px;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Core principles:</strong></div>
<ul class="KsbFXc U6u95" style="margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &#39;Google Sans&#39;, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; padding-inline-start: 16px;"><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Separation of concerns:</strong> The UI is completely decoupled from the assessment logic. The workspace component is purely for display and user interaction, while the scoring, validation, and data management remain on the server side.</span></li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Leverage existing data model:</strong> The solution reuses the existing GRC <code class="o8j0Mc" style="unicode-bidi: isolate; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; background-color: rgb(240, 242, 245); border-image: none 100% / 1 / 0 stretch; border-radius: 4px; padding: 2px 4px; border: 0.888889px solid rgb(240, 242, 245);">sn_grc_risk_assessment_factor_response</code> and related tables for storing assessment data, ensuring data integrity and consistency with standard reporting.</span></li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Scalable and maintainable:</strong> Developers build a custom component that is flexible enough to handle different assessment types without being hard-coded for specific risk factors.</span></li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Enhanced user experience:</strong> The custom component can implement dynamic behavior, advanced visualizations, and conditional logic that is impossible with the out-of-the-box (OOTB) component.</span></li></ul>
