<ul class="KsbFXc U6u95" style="margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: &#39;Google Sans&#39;, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; padding-inline-start: 16px;"><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Full customization:</strong> Developers gain complete control over the UI, user experience, and behavior of the assessment component, meeting any client requirement.</span></li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Maintainability:</strong> By using a custom component and a Scripted REST API, the solution is self-contained. Future platform upgrades are less likely to break the custom solution.</span></li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Scalability:</strong> The modular design allows for reusing the custom component with different assessment types by simply passing different data through the input properties.</span></li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Enhanced UX:</strong> Developers can build an intuitive, dynamic interface that guides users through the assessment process more effectively, leading to better data quality.</span></li><li style="margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; list-style-type: disc; padding-inline-start: 4px;"><span class="T286Pc" style="overflow-wrap: break-word;"><strong class="Yjhzub" style="font-weight: bold;">Future-proof:</strong> As UI Builder evolves, the custom component can be updated to leverage new features, while the core logic on the server remains untouched.</span></li></ul>
